CatDescriptText: Mrs. Annie Willis, 267 Williams Street, South Side, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 16, 1958, pg. 3 with question: "Do you think that Negroes are giving sufficient financial help to the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People?" answer reads: "I think that it could be better."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Annie Willis, wearing light colored skirt, light colored button down sleeveless blouse with vertical stripes, eyeglasses, and light colored double strand beaded necklace, standing on sidewalk with pedestrians, buildings, and storefront with sign inscribed "...sacrificing all summer merchandise save ...60..." in background
